text.section:
In this section, "inactive association" means a public watershed association established under this subtitle that for at least 5 years has not substantially complied with the majority of ordinary operating procedures required under this subtitle, including:
The maintenance of ongoing and current information in the watershed file at the Office of the Clerk of the Board of County Commissioners;
Elections of a board of directors and officers of the Board;
An annual meeting of owners of land within the association;
The submission of an annual report by the board of directors to the Clerk of the Board of County Commissioners;
The development, approval, appropriate filing, execution, or maintenance of a work plan applicable to property owned by the association; and
The submission and regular updating of the association's easement record in the office of the Clerk of the Circuit Court in the applicable county.
